rComments: talks about herself for the entire 3 hours. Entire course is marking you on your mental health and how much detail your willing go to into about personal issues. you write at least 4 pages weekly for reflections and assignments. graded on "attitude". I lost so many marks without explanation.

I really enjoy professor Fortier's classes! I've taken two of them - the work can get a little overwhelming as she does assign a lot of readings and reflections, but she is an easy marker so as long as you have good time management it's an easy A+. Her classes are very interactive and I genuinely think I learnt a lot of valuable lessons in them.

Professor Fortier tells students that she is here to support them & emphasizes good communication; however, she is extremely rude often and does not care about her students as much as she says she does. The class is extremely reading heavy and includes pointless reflections. She expects you to spend a ridiculous amount of time on work for the class
She's so nice and enthusiastic! A lot of work and reading but not hard material. Participation is required and some group work.
Such an amazing teacher! She is so caring of her students and wants to help them succeed not only in class but in life.

Slides are the most unclear of all my profs. Glares when you come to class late. Very interactive (getting up in front of the class etc), some group work/presentations on key topics (then you're tested on what the groups said), no midterm.

Slides are VERY unclear. Gave us two different documents and then said to the class "it's to complicated to explain, but it's going to be on the exam so I gave you the documents to look over"... On the final exam there were at least 5-6 questions about said documents that she did not explain in class.

Seems nice and is enthusiastic but it's research methods,the material is boring. She makes the class extremely interactive and demands that you be interactive. She grades participation and there's many inclass assignments to prevent you from skipping class. Also, her slides are hideous. They're tremendously unorganized; textbook is recommended.
